From db93eaf6e5e6120d8f14b6dde1faf450560320bf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Kol Crooks <kol.crooks@datadoghq.com>
Date: Tue, 5 May 2026 11:32:37 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] Phase 8: spinner during tour generation + token in/out usage
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Tour and Storyboard 'Generating chapters…' / 'Preparing…'
states now show an animated SVG spinner using the KRT accent.
Once generation completes, the live response's
`usage.input_tokens` (incl. cache read/creation) and
`usage.output_tokens` are surfaced in the Tour subheading
('· N in / M out') and the Storyboard header. Cached results
keep the existing '· cached' suffix instead — usage is a
property of the live API call, not the cached chapters.
